				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">why give him a mana pool at all?  give him a spell line up of spells like FireElementalNuke1 or whatever with a set cast time and 0 mana cost.  balance the nuke damage, casting time, resists, etc around that so the pet does a steady X DPS.  With focus it makes it so much easier to make this pet scale since level now goes up, example:
<br />

<br />
FirePetNuke
<br />

<br />
slot1: decrease Hp by 250(60) to 450(65)
<br />
slot2: decrease hate by 250(60) to 450(65)
<br />
mana: 0
<br />
casting time: 1
<br />
recast: 2
<br />
resist: -100 Fire
<br />

<br />

<br />
level 60 fire pet (unfocused) nukes for 250 every 3 seconds or 83~dps, each focus adds a level to the pet therefore increases his nuke dps to 150dps with GoD focus (makes pet 65th lvl).  i just threw those numbers out there but whatever, sounds about right in my non-expert opinion.  remove his ability to melee or taunt, give him earth pet lvl hp (for AEs) but crappy mitigation (he can't tank anyway).  Recast time is there because i don't remember if npcs have the standard 2.25 recast limitation on spells, if not, lower the DD and make it 0 sec recast so he just chain nukes.  concussion is there to prevent the pet from being summoned if he somehow got to top of aggro list since he'll probably be setup outside of melee range.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=754455" target="_blank" class="postlink">Elder Xuthaz Everhate</a>
