I understand, I was thinking more of from an ease of coding point of view.  RP aside with the wizard thing, there is already an absolute limitation on the DPS of the pet using my suggestion, and it's a heck of alot easier to code than retooling the focus items to add mana regen to the fire pet.  my idea lets the pet scale directly with focus effects.  about the melee thing, if the pet can melee, then the AI will tell it to enter melee range, and it will randomly decide to nuke as an NPC wizard and then nuke.  SoE's AI would gimp your pet, and there would be no reason to use it over any other standard melee pet since the fire pet would run into melee range anyway (like you would want to use a nuking pet against AE DD/ramp encounters, or encounters where push is a big issue, or the real estate on the ass end of the mob is tight and pets get in the way of your melees, etc)
