				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I dunno, i don't see a reason for the pet to use mana.  Mana and mana regen only serves as a limiter, and only if the pet is going to be using existing spells(which causes turmoil among wizards mainly), which means it won't be using the cool sustained DPS spell i described above.  Mana and mana regen will take longer for SoE to code and test and fix, if they bother with it at all.  They might just go "well we just fixed the focuses, pets are done til 3 expansions down the road, deal with it."  Then you have to worry about changing the focus items again so that they improve the fire pet as well.  whats it do? add more mana? or mana regen?  add more nukes? higher level dds?  it will be a hassle that has to be looked over every expansion as new focus items show up, which will inevitiably break melee pets, break the fire pet, break hp regen, or mana regen, etc etc.  This way, say next expansion a new focus comes along that will make the pet 66th level as well as add hp/hp regen/mitigation to pets.  all that is needed is to change is the Firepetnuke slot 1 and 2, to something like 
<br />
slot1: decrease Hp by 250(60) to 500(66) 
<br />
slot2: decrease hate by 250(60) to 500(66)
<br />

<br />
or whatever.  takes what, 2 minutes to make that change in the system?  of course, to ensure proper scaling, it'd probably be best that every level adds the same amount of DD to ease scaling, which means you'd need to change my original numbers around a bit, but you get the idea.
