				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The answer to fire pet woes is very simple:
<br />

<br />
Let the pet cast a nuke, say for the lvl 63 fire pet, a nuke doing 1200hp, make it *unresistable*. Thus the pet can land on bosses. NOTE this is *VERY* important since bosses are easily abover pets normal "level of ability to land spells on" cap.
<br />

<br />
Set the recast time for the pet so it's DPs is high, this pet should be the *raid* pet, this pet with whimp ass hps etc, but *NO* melee abilities, should generate around 90+ DPs. This pet cannot tank, it will not push, meaning on raids it owns, but in xp/solo it's not much use. Also in PvP it owudl kick ass, frankly mages suck at higher end PvP from what I can see (no low resist DDs of our own)
<br />

<br />
Ideally it should have poor melee and only use melee when the *pet itself is meleed against* but I don't trust coding on that being workable/easy to do.
<br />

<br />
As the pet gains levels form focus items, it's nuke damage raises accordingly.
<br />

<br />
There, we solve pet push, make fire pet worthwhile, help PvP, allows pet usable on AOE rmapage mobs and the like <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304331" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: red">REDORIOUS.....ARCHMAGE.....KARANA</span></span></a>
