				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hadn't thought about burst DPS, throws a kink in things i guess.  I'm not a magician so I won't pretend like i know what would be best, though if i needed burst i'd probably pop off HoE and SoR, where reasonable to do so, along with my fire pet's steady nuke dps, but you guys know what you need better than I.  I just can't think of a situation where having a high burst DPS nuke pet that has retarded AI and low DPS during downtime (current fire pet meleeing when lom) would be helpful over steady supply of high sustained DPS.  high burst is needed to stop a gater/runner, or to kill off a mob quick before the stuff hits the fan.  You'd basically have to stop what you are doing and summon the fire pet in order for him to start nuking right away for either of those conditions, which means you are summoning a pet instead of doing high burst DPS yourself.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Mana regen would need to be high, maybe add a +Mana component to all our heals. For instance Planar Renewal would give the pet 1200hp and 1200mana. Elemental Remedy (44 HoT, I think this is the correct name) would give 80hp/80mana per tick. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
