			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Neither HoE nor SoR really add a lot to burst damage, or any damage, for that matter.
<br />

<br />
HoE has too much push to use in a non-cornered mob situation. It also is decimated by any AoE or even DS on the mob. It also takes a full "casting time slot" to get off. Maxed, it is about 120 DPS for 30 seconds, so about 3600 damage -- less the 2000 or so damage you would have gotten from just casting a nuke.
<br />

<br />
SoR1 is good for about 900 damage on a good day, assuming no resists, so its only saving grace is it can be "popped" during spell-gem refresh.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
